  "markup": "\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELast Updated:\u003C/strong\u003E June 30, 2025\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPurpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To establish clear expectations for regular and punctual attendance, which is essential for meeting business objectives, ensuring smooth operations, providing excellent client service, and fostering effective teamwork.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWork Schedules:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Employees must adhere to their assigned work schedule, including start/end times and breaks, as determined by their manager. Any schedule changes require advance approval.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENotification of Absence/Lateness:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Employees unable to report to work or anticipating lateness must notify their immediate supervisor/manager as far in advance as possible (generally no later than one hour before scheduled start time, or end of prior shift, or as per department procedure). Do not rely on co-workers to deliver messages.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnreported Absences:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Absence for three (3) consecutive scheduled workdays without notification may be considered voluntary resignation, unless a satisfactory explanation is provided upon return.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbsences:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Absences are classified as excused (approved PTO, leaves, pre-approved by management, or legally required) or unexcused (without prior approval or proper notification). Excessive absenteeism, regardless of type (beyond legally protected leaves), may lead to disciplinary action.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateness:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Reporting late, returning late from breaks/lunch, or leaving early without approval is considered lateness and will be addressed.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedical Appointments:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Schedule medical appointments outside working hours if possible. If not, obtain prior manager approval and provide sufficient notice.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsequences of Violation\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Unplanned absences, excessive absenteeism, or repeated lateness will be addressed through progressive discipline, potentially leading to warnings, suspension, or termination.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E"
}]]></Value>
